caption: Fantastic food I love it all !!!

I wish I can give them zero stars!! They are extremely rude!! They don't have any patience. I asked them one question and they started yelling at me where is my wallet and we don't have time for questions. Plenty of places to eat in the area. You should go somewhere else.

A week ago I called and asked if they are kosher and they answered in very rude manner that they are not, they said “specifically trying to be non-kosher” very disappointed, it doesn’t make sense to call food vegan and have it cooked mixed with non-vegan food. Thanks.
Been there many times, good food, but one day owner was very rude and cocky, will not comeback. Do not suggest to go there, you deserve better treatment.
Incredible food and presentation!! Prices not bad, worth the value for sure. If you’re in the area, or just want good falafel, check it out
The Iraqi sandwich is incredible.
Go here and get the holy moly pita. Currently, my go to place. Welcome addition to the neighborhood.
Welcome to the neighborhood !! Hands down best Falafel I have ever had. It is made with respect for fresh food and dripping in kindness. The Tahina shake is everything! Bravo. Thank you!!!!
Great food, a blend of Iraqi Israeli and other middle eastern. Always get the Harissa sauce.
Absolutely the best falafel in the city...maybe the country. And not just falafel...a carefully curated menu of mid-eastern fare ...and a very pleasant patio in the back as well.
They make an incredible Schwarma in a pita I go there once or twice a week it's so good
Outstanding falafel!!! Truly delicious. Highly recommend.
Very slow for one order

The food is so delicious and fresh...BUT why no masks?! Been in there twice and nobody there had a mask on. Went to pop in tonight but again, the owner and 2 other folks gabbing inside with no masks so took our business elsewhere. Will still support and still love the food but come on 😬

The best Mediterranean food I have ever had in New York. The owner, Josh, is a food prodigy as he is an amazing host. What a gem of a place, I stop by every opportunity I get. The back yard makes this place a wonderful hanging spot for outside dining. I would give it a 6th star if I could. Must visit !!!!!
Love the falafel pita!! Took it to go and it was amazing. Filling, full of flavor, and highly recommend.
Good falafel, selection of things you can find in an Israeli street kiosk. Slightly high-end interms of preparation and presentation

Wow, just a great neighborhood spot. The guy who owns it is super friendly and kind of hilarious and the food is consistently awesome (try the Iraqi and any of the pita sandwiches). Support your local joint!
The food is delicious, Prices are easy on the pocket and they make the most divine shakes.  Try the Date Shake😋

Always looking for a good falafel in the neighborhood and finally found it!!!! We got falafel sandwiches, sumac fries, and Moroccan cigars and all were on point! Also really fast delivery :) thank you - this will be our new regular spot :)
So happy to find this restaurant! Great service, tastes good, packed well and arrived quickly 👍
delicious food and wonderful service!!!! 💕💕💕 a new favorite :)
Tasty falafel, great backyard area and a taste tester named Pita.
The nicest falafel I can remember eating. Patio is perfect for these socially distanced times.

To call Holy Pita a neighborhood gem doesn't do it justice. Take the ferry to the Navy Yard, hop off the cycling Greenway on your way to/from Williamsburg, or get off the BQE to come visit. Literally everything on the menu is terrific and Josh, the owner, is a character and a charmer.  Save room for dessert.
Nice place, nice food, nice everything 🥰😬😃

Dropped in to pick up some fresh pitas, stayed and had a fantastic experience. The space is wonderfully decorated with an enchanting backyard space. The owner was SO friendly and had me try a few falafel balls on the house (just like they do it in Israel). I have to say- one of, if not THE most perfect falafels I have had in my life. The tahini, the pita, the hot sauce... all stunningly fresh and delicious. I cannot WAIT to come back and try the entire menu and dine in the backyard with friends!!! Transported me back to Tel Aviv. The real deal.

The food and the hospitality were equally great.  Truly.  We had the sabich, moroccan cigars (veggie) and the hummus.  Then we sampled the vegan shawarma and falafel.  5 stars all around.  Thanks, Josh!

Absolutely delicious!! The pita bread itself was so spongey and soft! The falafel, chicken shawarma and even the rice were all exceptional. Definitely get the spicy harif sauce. Plan to come back real soon!
Yes. It’s very good. Not afraid of the spices and heat. You should go.
Delicious food. Had the malawach, and the bread was so delicious. Great vibes

This restaurant is delicious authentic food! The staff is very friendly, there is a beautiful backyard area to eat and hangout in as well. Falafel are so perfect! Not dry at all. Can't wait until next time.
Nice

Dining alfresco!! Love all the flavorful, fresh ingredients this food gives me life along with the charming, electric, charismatic owner.  The comfortable and beautiful backyard is perfect for current times. Dine in or take it to go. You're in for some WAP; Wet A$$ Pita, that's always crisp and crunchy, never soggy.  The beer and wine offerings hit the spot as well. I got the sparkling rosé and it was neither too dry nor too sweet. You know I had to grab some  baklava on my way out the door.
Delicious food & great back garden

This place is delicious! Fresh, flavorful, authentic and healthy. They take pride in their food and service. The backyard is perfect for lunch or casual dinner, takeout is equally quality. Major upgrade to the neighborhood food options.
Excellent food! Great outdoor seating..enjoy

Come here to enjoy some contemporary Israeli foods: hummus, falafel, sabich and more. Mostly vegetarian but carnivores will get their options as well. Grab a draft beer abs experience the authentic atmosphere in the patio at the back. Prices are as expected. Just a few minutes walk from the ferry pier so you can enjoy a scenic ride before or after your meal.
Holy Pita is amazing. Food wise, meals are fantastic and served in large servings. Owner is super friendly. Singled handedly  saved summer 2020 despite COVID.  Tip: get the chicken shawarma sandwich

Fantastic new spot just off flushing ave. The backyard area is incredible with plenty of space. Dog friendly (the owners dog Pita is very sweet). I got the chicken shawarma, and look forward to trying the hummus and cigars next trip.

I tried Holy Pita for the first time yesterday and all I can say is WOW. So good! Such a nice addition to the neighborhood. The Chicken Shawarma is out of this world. So flavorful, so tasty, and everything just tastes so fresh. They have a really nice backyard seating area that is spacious and really well furnished. It’s a super cool spot to hang out at and even once you’re done eating, it’s nice just to relax and have a beer in the nice garden environment. They have great beers on draft – we had a summer ale, which was delicious and beers are reasonably priced at $6, which is really nice. The staff is super friendly and I absolutely cannot wait to have another meal here. It will be very soon!

The real deal. If you're craving Israeli-styled middle eastern fare, original dishes, vegetarian food or just a really good meal, look no further. A quick pita sandwich or a full size platter, you'll find fantastic food here. The backyard outdoor seating complements the authentic cooking and atmosphere. An instant favorite.

All I have to say is wow. Best falafel I had in my life. All Ingredients are super fresh and that is reminded in every bite you take. The staff is super hospitable and everything was super clean. The backyard makes this place a absolute gem. Quality of ingredients for the win. I am obsessed. I love the schnitzel salad, the pickles cabbage, falafel and malawa I think it’s called (crispy flat bread), yogurt, and draft beer selection.
Amazing food and service!
The falafel sandwich is good and abundant, you might have to save you coins on making it spicy because it gets loss in the herbs..  or maybe my Caribbean taste buds cant taste them
Get the sabich. Or anything else. This place is amazing.
Eating here made me feel like I was back in Tel Aviv.  By far the best, most authentic, Israeli street food I've had in New York
Great food! Owner was so friendly 😊
Truly amazing authentic food & super friendly owner!

I’ve now been here two weeks in a row and I think this may be my go-to Saturday late lunch spot. The owner Josh is a joy to hang out with and I spent 2.5 hours just having going out today. Food is fresh and delicious and I highly recommend this place.
Great spot. Coming back again. You’ll feel at home. Chill and cool spot to have a few beers and food with friends.
Everything was delicious. Try the Iraqi for sure.
Chicken Shawarma was savory and well-spiced. Lots of flavors and quality ingredients
Delicious, fresh, flavorful food! Beautiful, shady back patio and safe social distance measures being taken. Will be back!
This place is sooooo good. Highly recommend. Exceptional food and a welcoming, friendly place to visit.
Fresh, delicious food and friendly service. Try the falafel, chicken shawarma, and schnitzel. You won’t regret eating here!

Delicious food, lovely outdoor back patio, and very friendly owner/staff. Everything is made in-house. The chicken shawarma over basmati rice was seasoned perfectly and bursting with flavor, the pita was soft, and the hummus was fresh and creamy.
Highly recommended! The food was absolutely delicious, the outside seating is super quiet and inviting and most importantly the staff were awesome! Will go back again soon! 🥙🥗🙏🏼
Fantastic food, so friendly and nice backyard.   This is a great place to grab a bite in the area.   Also you can have a cold beer in backyard outdoors.  Must visit.

This new restaurant is a stellar welcome addition to the neighborhood. Everything we have tried has been absolutely delicious particularly the chicken Shawarma and the Moroccan  cigars filled with meat. Every ingredient is carefully prepared and layered to create some of the best food around and at great prices. We have been back 3 times since discovering it a little over a week ago. And the back patio is lovely.

Picked up a couple of falafel sandwiches to go. Very good. Sumac fries also good. Both the fries and the sandwiches travelled well - not soggy. The harif sauce is hot and flavorful. Will definitely be back.
Super delicious. Had the shawarma pita and chicken shawarma salad and they were both great. Amazing ingredients, and really fresh. This place is a great addition to the neighborhood!

Really delicious new middle eastern spot! Had the chicken shawarma salad and it was so good. Sat in their cute, clean and not crowded backyard. Highly recommend checking it out! Also, the owner came and gave us a taste of their falafel - I’m definitely getting that next time around 🤤

This place is an absolute gem. I’ve been 3 times because it’s in my neighborhood, and every time I’m blown away by the flavors and freshness. This is a big statement, but this THE BEST FALAFEL I’VE EVER HAD! But this place is more than just a falafel joint, Josh the owner and chef serves many highlights from Mediterranean and middle eastern fare. In this picture I had the falafel sandwich, the veggie moroccan cigars, and kubeh. All 3 were spectacular, Highly recommend. This place is a little off the beaten path but well worth it. They have a great backyard patio and serve local beer on draft and wine.

My new favorite spot in the Navy Yards area and probably one of my favorite Mediterranean food places in the city! Everything we had was fantastic and made by a real chef! We had the Sabich and the Malawach and they were both so delicious. Can’t wait to go back again!

Wow! Found out about this place today and went there for lunch. What a phenomenal hummus and falafel! I really enjoyed the meal and will be back whenever I can. If you want to experience a real Israeli hummus experience - this is the place.

We ordered the labneh pita sandwich, Moroccan meat cigars, side of chicken shawarma, date tahini shake, sumac fries, and the kuban. My labneh pita sandwich was mouth watering goodness. If you know you enjoy labneh and pickles and Israeli salad omg sooo yummy. I ordered on seamless my delivery came fast and the food was all fresh and aromatic. I also really enjoyed and recommend the meat cigars.  They were delicious.  Great food and fast accurate delivery.  I will definitely be ordering again soon or stopping by.
Love the hummus tahini, cute backyard and good vibe. Would eat again

Amazing new place close to my house with delicious middle eastern food! We had Sabish and chicken shawarma pita sandwiches! Almost ate my tongue how awesome it was! The staff is very friendly and welcoming! Backyard takes you to warm chill summer evenings with fresh craft beer and awesome music! Will come in again! Highly recommended!

So blessed to find Holy Pita!  Walked from Wegman's to find new restaurant Holy Pita open and very welcoming. Sat socially distanced in back courtyard and dined on delicious shawarma chicken pita.  Will come again. The owner personally greeted us and shared that all items are made fresh daily including the pita bread.  And it showed.  Thank you Josh for making our date night special!

While Holy Pita is a new local spot, my partner and I have already been here 3-4 times! The staff is so friendly and the chef/owner himself has recommended a few items during my visits. Overall the food is flavorful, savory, and fresh. From their Bites, I've tried the Kubeh, Moroccan Cigars, and Sumac Fries - seasoned with great authentic spices and sauces to die for like the their house hot sauce ('harif'). From their Salads, I loved the Sabich Salad and Schnitzel Salad - fresh and healthy green mixes balanced with tahina and a lemony-tangy dressing on the side. My boyfriend is the biggest sweet tooth so I can't forget to call out their Sweet Chocolate Malawach and Tahina Shakes (try the date one!) - you can't find these anywhere else! This will continue to be my go-to spot in the neighborhood! Lastly, the selection of craft beers and backyard area is perfect to take some time to relax and enjoy the summer.

I was here the other day and it was spectacular!!! My girlfriend and I had the falafel sandwich and the shnitzel salad, I had a beer, and she had a tahina shake (first time I ever heard of such a thing but it was soooooo good). I went to sleep that night just wanting more of those flavors in my mouth. We will probably go back today or tomorrow again, I need more of that freshness. Thanks Josh for the great service and awesome food! Love that awesome Harif sauce!

Ask the chef owner why his malawach is like sex. Then order it and be prepared. Also find the smoothest hummus in Brooklyn. Why?: 24 hour soak followed by 12 hours of boiling and all the skins are peeled. Highly recommend. Catch me in the back yard having a beer after work this summer.
